main event: The document consists of various pages from a Project Blue Book report, detailing witness observations of a UFO sighting in Elizabethtown, Kentucky on September 11, 1952. The witness described seeing a sphere or ellipse-shaped object in the sky, revolving and appearing to glow or be phosphorescent. The report includes details about the witness and the circumstances of the sighting, as well as a hand-drawn sketch of the observed object's motion and shape.
interesting points: The witness saw a sphere or ellipse-shaped object in the sky, which seemed to be revolving and emitting a glow or phosphorescent light.

The witness, a 33-year-old male salesman, reported seeing the object while driving in a car with his family, and mentioned that the object appeared to be flying at a very high rate of speed and at a high altitude, with erratic movement and the ability to change direction abruptly.
The witness reported that the object emitted a weird roaring noise, and that the motor of their car was running at the time of the sighting.

Another page of the report mentioned a separate incident where an object reportedly contacted a car, carrying it across the ground for a considerable distance, and rendering the occupant unconscious, leaving the car subjected to intense heat with various parts apparently affected.

The report includes a letter from the Air Technical Intelligence Center at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, acknowledging the witness's report of unidentified aerial phenomena and providing a questionnaire for further evaluation of the data.
sighted object: a sphere or ellipse-shaped object emitting a glow or phosphorescent light
witnesses: A 33-year-old male salesman and other unnamed witnesses
